# Architecture & typing

- Backend is Python 3.12 + FastAPI + Pydantic v2 + SQLAlchemy 2.0, managed with `uv`.
- Use type hints everywhere (mypy --strict friendly). Prefer dataclasses/Pydantic models.
- Small, focused functions; minimal nesting (guard clauses); no duplication or dead code.
- Separate concerns: business logic / IO & APIs / data access / external services.
- Provider integrations go through the existing factory + registry abstractions with
  explicit mock fallbacks. Do not bypass provider boundaries.
- Follow Ruff config (line-length 100, py312). No hardcoded values where config belongs.
